    "created_at": "2017-06-26T05:47:54Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-06-26T05:47:54Z",
    "body": "Hi, thanks for this, but having an example injecting global variables and then claiming it is not secure probably just indicates we should not have the example at all.\r\n\r\nThe documentation already covers everything users would need, for usage tips like this it is probably more suitable to be a blog post, otherwise the documentation would be rather long filled with various tricks users could use (JavaScript is a rather tricky language).\r\n\r\nSo I'm closing this."
